Job Details
ONLY APPLY WITH FEEDBACK ON BELOW REQUIREMENTS OTHERWISE YOUR APPLICATION NOT ACCEPTED Managing, leading and inspiring the team so to achieve the desired objectives. Planning and monitoring objectives, budgets, schedules and resource to ensure organizational goals and targets are met.Making a significant contribution to the profitability of the division. Achieving and maintaining company Policies and Objectives.Establishing client base by prospecting and building relationships.Ensuring profitability by using technical and commercial skills.Fostering teamwork for maximizing productivity and efficiency.Any other responsibility, authority & communication which is required  for this position  is automatically assumed.
Requirements
Requirements  Education: Graduate/Diploma in Mechanical /Automobile Engineering. Experience: At least 10 years in similar industry and the last 2 years in similar position. Age: 35-45 preferred
Must have thorough knowledge of EuropeanJapaneseAmerican   Automobiles
COMMUNICATIONS Monthly Sales ProjectionsMonthly Sales and profitability reportsStock reportsAny other MIS report deemed necessary.Key result areaSales and Gross Profitability growth.Cost and overhead controlOptimization of  ResourcesBusiness Development.
